com.siperian.sif.message.metadata

Class MetaDataHmPackage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataBase
      • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataHmPackage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable

    public class MetaDataHmPackage
extends MetaDataBase
    Represents a HM package. An HM package is used to perform operations on HM entities and relationships as dictated by the usage type.
    See Also:
    DescribeSiperianObjectRequest, Serialized Form

    API Group: Metadata

      • setRelTypeName

        public void setRelTypeName(String relTypeName)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        relTypeName - Name of the HM relationship type that this HM package is for. It is used to create the relationship type UID. Either the relationship type or entity type must be associated with a HM package.
        See Also:
        getRelTypeUid()

      • setRelTypeUid

        public void setRelTypeUid(String relTypeUid)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        relTypeUid - UID of HM relationship type that this HM package is for. Either the relationship type or entity type must be associated with a HM package.
        See Also:
        getRelTypeUid()

      • getRelTypeUid

        public String getRelTypeUid()
        Get the UID that identifies the relationship type that this HM package belongs to. The result will be null if this HM package is for an entity type.
        Returns:
        UID of HM relationship type that this HM package is for or null

      • setEntityTypeName

        public void setEntityTypeName(String entityTypeName)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        entityTypeName - name of the HM entity type that this HM package is for. It is used to create the entity type UID. Either the relationship type or entity type must be associated with a HM package.
        See Also:
        getEntityTypeUid()

        public void setEntityTypeUid(String entityTypeUid)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        entityTypeUid - UID of HM entity type that this HM package is for. Either the relationship type or entity type must be associated with a HM package.
        See Also:
        getEntityTypeUid()

      • getEntityTypeUid

        public String getEntityTypeUid()
        Get the UID that identifies the entity type that this HM package belongs to. The result will be null if this HM package is for an relationship type.
        Returns:
        UID of HM entity type that this HM package is for or null

      • setUsageType

        public void setUsageType(String pkgUsageType)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        pkgUsageType - What this HM package is used for. Must be one of MetaDataHmPackage.PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values.
        See Also:
        getUsageType()

      • getUsageType

        public String getUsageType()
        Get the usage type for this HM package. The usage type will one of the PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values defined in this class.
        Returns:
        What this HM package is used for. Will be one of MetaDataHmPackage.PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values.

        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.

        column - Column to be added to this HM package.
        Returns:
        Value returned by Set.add() method.
        See Also:

      • setColumns

        public void setColumns(SortedSet columns)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        columns - the columns for this HM package. The objects in the SortedSet should be of MetaDataTableColumn type. The SortedSet cannot be null and must have one or more elements.
        See Also:
        getColumns()

      • getColumns

        public SortedSet getColumns()
        Get the SortedSet of MetaDataTableColumn objects that make up the columns of this HM package. The columns are sorted in order of their sequence.
        Returns:
        Columns for this HM package. The objects in the SortedSet will be of MetaDataTableColumn type. The SortedSet can never be null and will have one or more elements.

      • getColumnUids

        public List getColumnUids()
        Get the List of UIDs that represent the columns of this HM package. The UIDs are sorted in order of the column sequence.
        Returns:
        List (never null) of Column UIDs (String objects) in the order of their sequence in this HM package.
